UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1759
1 A RESOLUTION honoring Frank Riherd, founder of the Riherd's Scoreboard, for
2 his enduring contributions to Kentucky high school athletics.
3 WHEREAS, native of Glasgow, Kentucky, Frank Riherd's family owned a sporting
4 goods store in his hometown; and
5 WHEREAS, after travelling to Louisville in 1968 as a high school freshman to see
6 his Glasgow Scotties capture the Kentucky High School Athletic Association (KHSAA)
7 boys' basketball championship, Frank Riherd became enthralled with numbers that
8 surrounded sports and proceeded to keep statistics for the Glasgow basketball and
9 football teams the next year; and
10 WHEREAS, after graduating from Glasgow High School, Frank Riherd attended
11 Georgia Institute of Technology, where he studied electrical engineering and worked
12 developing software that would collect and analyze data from radar systems; and
13 WHEREAS, Frank Riherd's career as an electrical engineer led him across the
14 globe, from California, to Germany, and eventually to France, where he worked for VLSI
15 Technology before striking out on his own as a consultant in 1996; and
16 WHEREAS, during a visit home to Glasgow in early 1997, he sold his father on an
17 idea for a trophy order website for the sporting goods store, and also approached the
18 KHSAA about establishing an online scoreboard to disseminate high school sports
19 information at the user's convenience; and
20 WHEREAS, the Riherd's Scoreboard officially kicked off in the fall of 1997, and as
21 the operation grew and flourished, it has become the historical repository of high school
22 sports information in the Commonwealth; and
23 WHEREAS, since 1997, the Riherd's Scoreboard, which now covers 12 boys' and
24 girls' sports, has recorded over 650,000 games representing almost 30 million points,
25 runs, and goals scored by prep athletes from every corner of Kentucky; and
26 WHEREAS, the importance of this endeavor was perhaps best explained by Frank
27 Riherd himself, when he said, "Each of those points comes from a player competing as
Page 1 of 3
