UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1759
1 part of a team. And we should never lose sight of the fact that they are the reason we do
2 all of this. That's our North Star — the athlete"; and
3 WHEREAS, on January 10, 2026, Frank Riherd announced that the 2025-2026
4 school year will be his last managing the scoreboards; and
5 WHEREAS, news of Frank Riherd stepping away from the scoreboard he has made
6 his life's work was met with sadness and deep appreciation from all corners of the
7 Commonwealth, with KHSAA Commissioner Julian Tackett summing up the feelings of
8 many when he said, "He’s been a fixture in our association for a long time. We really
9 express our love and affection for him as well as our respect for the professional work
10 he’s done on behalf of our membership"; and
11 WHEREAS, Zack Klemme, the sports director for HD Media, with 13 newspapers
12 in Kentucky, Virginia, West Virginia, and Ohio, also lauded Frank Riherd's work: "The
13 KHSAA website and scoreboard is the gold standard for access to information and ease
14 of use. I am thankful for the role Frank Riherd has played for 15 years in making my life
15 easier and making my work better"; and
16 WHEREAS, the KHSAA has pledged to continue the scoreboard, and although the
17 service will undoubtedly continue, the vision, passion, and foresight of Frank Riherd and
18 the indelible mark he has made on high school athletics in the Commonwealth will never
19 be forgotten and is certainly worthy of public recognition;
20 NOW, THEREFORE,
21 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
22 Kentucky:
23 Section 1. The members of the Senate join Senator David Givens in honoring
24 Frank Riherd for developing and operating the Riherd's Scoreboard, applauding the
25 positive impact he has had on generations of high school athletes in the Commonwealth,
26 and expressing their deep appreciation for his years of hard work involved in this
27 endeavor.
